# Chirag, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Chirag (; Aghul: Хьургъни) is a rural locality (a selo) in Agulsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 545 as of 2010.
Geography
Chirag is located on the Chiragchay River, 19&nbsp;km northwest of Tpig (the district's administrative centre) by road. Richa is the nearest rural locality.
